{"name":"Andersen - The Commander","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-barbute-rivited-steel.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Captain Andersen is a former Carolean commander and war hero who led his company through the bloody Swedish-Russian war. Six years ago, driven by jealousy and strict religious discipline, he ordered the brutal punishment of Private Enar—cutting off his leg and throwing him into the sea—for deserting to be with Satu, a dancer Andersen himself secretly loved. After the execution, overcome with obsession, Andersen raped Satu, resulting in the birth of his son Erik. Now a wealthy retired officer living on his estate near Borgholm, Andersen is haunted by guilt. He has sought out Satu, freed her from poverty, and brought her and Erik to live with him, desperately trying to earn her forgiveness and build a family. But Enar has returned as an immortal monster bent on revenge, and Andersen must defend his newfound happiness while hiding the shameful truth of his past crimes from everyone, including his former soldiers.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills","I am a capable fighter trained in Carolean military tactics","I carry the weight of terrible sins from my past","I will do anything to protect my new family"],"gifts":[{"name":"Commander","description":"Andersen is skilled at giving orders and managing a battle. **Tactical Orders:** Up to 3 times per Scene, Andersen can issue an order to an ally. The ally receives 1 Additional Success when executing that order (+1 to Opposition Level in the case of an NPC). **Coordinated Defense:** Allies fighting alongside Andersen within 30 feet can use his tactical advice to improve their positioning and timing."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Defend my new family from the danger that Enar represents","Redeem myself in the eyes of Satu and make her understand that I am now a different man","Prevent anyone from discovering what I have done"],"notes":"Andersen is a complex antagonist/ally who committed horrible crimes (ordering Enar's execution, raping Satu) but genuinely seeks redemption. He loves Erik deeply and has changed, but his past sins are inescapable. Voice: Commanding but with undertones of regret. If Erik is endangered, Andersen will confess everything to save him. If the Hunters learn the truth, he may become suicidal or attempt to sacrifice himself. Works well with Christian (his most loyal soldier). Has over 20 servants on his estate but only he and Christian are skilled fighters."},"_id":"d36808f68c95461c"}
{"name":"Christian - The Relentless","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-barbute-black.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"Christian earned the nickname \"the Relentless\" during the Swedish-Russian war for his cold determination and unwavering execution of orders. He was one of the six surviving Caroleans who participated in Enar's punishment six years ago, though he was unaware of Andersen's personal motivations—he simply followed orders as he always does. Christian never fully adapted to civilian life and still carries himself like a soldier, always ready for the next mission. When Andersen called for help against the mysterious monster killing their former comrades, Christian immediately answered, driven by loyalty to his old commander and a desire to prove himself the better man by eliminating Enar. He is stationed at Andersen's estate as part of the defense force. Christian's greatest strength—his absolute obedience to orders—is also his weakness, as he never questions the morality of his actions.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a former soldier called the Relentless by all because of my cold determination","I act without any qualms when it comes to executing an order","I never question my commander's decisions","I am still a soldier in my heart, even in civilian clothes"],"gifts":[{"name":"The Relentless","description":"When carrying out an order, Christian becomes an unstoppable force. **Iron Will:** Christian is immune to any effect that affects his behavior while executing orders, such as fear, charm, confusion, or mind control. **Unwavering Focus:** Christian increases his Opposition Level by +1 when he tries to eliminate an obstacle that stands between him and the subject of an order he must carry out. **Single-Minded:** Once given an order, Christian will not stop until it is completed or he is incapacitated."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Help Andersen in memory of the old days and a military life I can't forget","Eliminate Enar to prove I am the better man","Follow orders without question, as a good soldier should"],"notes":"Christian is loyal to a fault and represents military discipline taken to an extreme. He participated in Enar's execution without remorse because it was an order. Voice: Curt, military, emotionless. If Enar attacks on Day 1 and Hunters aren't present, Christian dies defending the estate. If sent to investigate the cliff on Day 2 without Hunters, the Sea Fairy will kill him for his role in Enar's death. He works seamlessly with Andersen, anticipating orders. Never wavers or shows doubt."},"_id":"ee7444c3fea8301c"}
{"name":"Hans - The Gunslinger","type":"npc","img":"icons/weapons/guns/gun-pistol-flintlock.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"Hans was one of the company's best marksmen during the war, famous for never missing his mark. He invested more than half his war earnings in a pair of experimental pistols from an inventor—guns that can fire multiple shots without reloading. He always keeps them hidden under his heavy overcoat along with smoke bombs for tactical advantage. Hans was one of the six survivors who participated in Enar's execution six years ago. Unlike the others, Hans is primarily concerned with keeping the secret of what they did to Enar. When the mysterious murders began, Hans grew paranoid about Nils, the Poor Devil, who has been showing signs of guilt and might confess to the authorities. On Day 1, Hans travels to Sundsvall with the intent to interrogate Nils and, if necessary, silence him permanently. Hans is ruthless, practical, and willing to kill to protect himself and his reputation. He views Nils's conscience as a liability that must be eliminated.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":4,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a former soldier, once one of the company's best marksmen","I never miss my mark","I always have a loaded weapon hidden under my heavy overcoat","I will do whatever it takes to protect my secrets"],"gifts":[{"name":"Gunslinger","description":"Hans owns a pair of prized experimental pistols bought from an inventor. **Rapid Fire:** Hans's guns can fire multiple shots simultaneously. With one attack, Hans can aim at up to 3 targets within a 30-foot square area. **Reload Master:** While firing one pistol, Hans can reload the other as an additional action without penalty. **Quick Draw:** When Hans draws a pistol from under his coat, he can make an immediate attack with Opposition Level Hard 7, catching enemies off-guard. **Marksman:** Hans receives +1 Additional Success when making called shots or targeting specific body parts."},{"name":"Smoke Bombs","description":"Hans carries smoke bombs for tactical advantage. **Deploy Smoke:** While firing a pistol, Hans can drop a smoke bomb as an additional action. **Thick Smoke:** The smoke covers a 30-foot square area. Everyone inside receives 1 Penalty for every action requiring sight, except Hans who is immune. **Tactical Escape:** Hans can always disengage from opponents in the smoke without anyone preventing him, slipping away unseen. **Duration:** Smoke lasts for the remainder of the Scene or until dispersed by strong wind."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Convince Nils to keep our secret or remove him","Survive this nightmare by eliminating threats before they eliminate me","Protect my reputation and freedom at any cost"],"notes":"Hans is morally grey—willing to murder Nils to keep secrets. Voice: Quiet, calculating, paranoid undertones. On Day 1, if Hunters aren't in Sundsvall, Hans kills Nils. On Day 2, if Hans killed Nils, he ambushes Enar in Sundsvall but dies in the fight. If Nils is alive on Day 2, Enar attacks Nils and Hans may help defend. His experimental pistols are his pride—losing them would devastate him. Uses smoke bombs tactically to control battlefield. Sees conscience as weakness."},"_id":"89ca07cbe4c74873"}
{"name":"Nils - The Poor Devil","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/leg/greaves-armored-steel.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Old Nils earned the nickname \"the Poor Devil\" after losing both his legs in the war between Sweden and Russia. Despite his disability and the hardships he endured, Nils invested his war earnings wisely and donated much of his wealth to the neediest in his community of Sundsvall, where he is beloved by all. He was one of the six surviving Caroleans who participated in Enar's punishment six years ago, and unlike his comrades, the guilt has never left him. Nils kept a detailed diary documenting everything that happened—how they judged Enar for desertion, how Captain Andersen ordered his leg cut off and his body thrown into the sea, and how the punishment seemed excessive and cruel. Though Nils doesn't know about Andersen's rape of Satu (that secret was kept even from the soldiers), he senses the injustice of what they did. When the mysterious murders began killing his former comrades one by one, Nils's guilt told him the truth: Enar has returned for revenge. Unable to move due to his injuries and unwilling to see more bloodshed, Nils reached out through his network of friends to summon the Order of Hunters, hoping they can stop Enar and bring peace to his tormented former brother-in-arms. But Hans is coming to silence him, and Enar is coming for revenge.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am an old soldier who lost his legs in the war","I am beloved in my community for my generosity","I am haunted by guilt for what we did to Enar","I have many friends and connections who would help me"],"gifts":[],"conditions":[],"agenda":["The guilt for what we did to Enar haunts me, I want to find a way to bring him peace","Tell the truth about what happened six years ago, no matter the consequences","Protect my community from the violence that has followed us home from the war"],"notes":"Nils represents conscience and redemption. He summoned the Hunters because he believes Enar deserves peace, not just to be killed again. Voice: Tired, remorseful, wise. His diary in Sundsvall reveals Enar's identity, his relationship with Satu, and details of the execution—but NOT Andersen's rape. On Day 1, Hans arrives to interrogate him; if Hunters aren't present, Hans kills him. On Day 2, if alive, Enar comes for him; if Hunters aren't present, Enar kills him. His house is modest despite his wealth. He cannot walk and uses a wheelchair or crutches. Respected elder figure who could testify about Andersen's crimes if he survives."},"_id":"22207a00da2b3da6"}